[13:18] <masak> there are three major categories of Q node types -- everything belonging to the expression language (Q::Expr), everything belonging to the statement language (Q::Statement), and then various other minor things like traits
[13:20] <masak> it's not *wrong* a priori to try to inject a trait using a macro, but the only place it'll ever have any chance of succeeding is inside an unquote: {{{ trait_producing_macro() }}}
